In a speech at Langley Research Center, Vice President Mike Pence expressed his support for American leadership in space exploration. He highlighted the achievements of the center, including its role in the Apollo missions and the development of advanced technologies. Pence also emphasized the Trump administration's commitment to returning American astronauts to the Moon within the next five years and eventually establishing a presence on Mars. He praised the collaboration between government and private sector partners and emphasized the need for innovation and collaboration to achieve these goals. Pence assured the audience that NASA and Langley Research Center would have the necessary resources and support to accomplish their mission. He encouraged the center's employees to continue their pioneering work and challenged them to engage with the private sector to bring new ideas and perspectives to the table. Pence concluded his speech by expressing his faith in the capabilities of the American people and their ability to accomplish any mission when they set their minds to it.